								<h1>News</h1><div><div class="news"><div class="newsimg"></div><h4>The second MACFINROBODS conference in Brussels, 20-21 June 2016</h4><p class="date"><i>2016-01-12</i></p><p>Keynote speakers: Chris Sims (Princeton University), Stephanie Schmitt-Grohé (Columbia University) and Philippe Bacchetta (Université de Lausanne)</p><p class="read-more simple"><a href="/news/11/the_second_macfinrobods_conference_in_brussels_20-21_june_2016.html">Read more</a></p><hr/></div></div>							</div>
								<div class="col-sm-6">
									<h1>Events</h1><div><div class="block"><div class="cal inactive future"><div class="cal-row"><div class="left"><span class="weekday">ma</span><span class="day">20</span><span class="month">jun</span></div><h4 class="plaats">Second Annual Dissemination Conference</h4><span class="locatie">National Bank of Belgium  - Brussels</span></div><div class="omschrijving"><h3>20-12 June 2016</h3><p><span style="color: rgb(114, 114, 114); font-family: Lato, serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 0.3px; line-height: 26px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The second </span><span style="color: rgb(98, 98, 98); font-family: Lato, serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 0.3px; line-height: 26px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Annual Dissemination Conference</span><span style="color: rgb(114, 114, 114); font-family: Lato, serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 0.3px; line-height: 26px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp;will be jointly&nbsp;organized by the National Bank of Belgium (NBB/BNB), Universit&eacute; Libre de Bruxelles (ULB) and Catholic University Leuven (KUL) on 20 and 21 June 2016.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p>Keynote speakers:<br />
Chris Sims (Princeton University)</p>

<p>Stephanie Schmitt-Groh&eacute; (Columbia University)</p>

<p>Philippe Bacchetta (Universit&eacute; de Lausanne)</p>
</div></div></div><hr/><div class="block"><div class="cal inactive future"><div class="cal-row"><div class="left"><span class="weekday">ma</span><span class="day">30</span><span class="month">nov</span></div><h4 class="plaats">Second MACFINROBODS Scientific Workshop</h4><span class="locatie">Institut d&#039;Anàlisi Econòmica, CSIC - BARCELONA</span></div><div class="omschrijving"><h3>30 November and 1 December 2015</h3><p>The Second &nbsp;Consortium Scientific Workshop was held at Institut d&#39;An&agrave;lisi Econ&ograve;mica (CSIC) in Barcelona, Spain, &nbsp;on 30 November and 1 December 2015. It was a very successful two-day event with over 45 participants. There were 12 presentations by senior- and young researchers from all teams and two very inspiring keynote lectures by <strong>Jordi Gal&iacute;</strong>, CREI and Universitat Pompeu Fabra and <strong>Juan Pablo Nicolini</strong>, Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis. A poster session for earlier-stage works of the network was organized just after lunch on the second day of the Workshop. There were 7 poster presentations &nbsp;by junior faculty mainly. It was a great opportunity for those presenting with all senior people attending, participating, asking around and giving comments.</p>

<p>Download Pdf file of the Workshop program <a href="/files/files/Program-27november(1).pdf">here</a></p>
</div></div></div><hr/><div class="block"><div class="cal inactive future"><div class="cal-row"><div class="left"><span class="weekday">ma</span><span class="day">15</span><span class="month">jun</span></div><h4 class="plaats">First Annual Dissemination Conference</h4><span class="locatie">Banque de France - PARIS</span></div><div class="omschrijving"><h3>15 -16 June 2015</h3><p>The First Annual Dissemination Conference was held at Banque de France in Paris, France on 15-16 June 2015. It was a very successful two-day event with over 60 participants. The conference started with a welcome speech given by Alain Duchateau, the general deputy director of Banque de France.</p>

<p>There were 11 presentations of advanced-stage papers from all teams and a poster session including 9 presentations of early-stage works. We also had 3 inspiring keynote lectures. The first keynote lecture was given by Thomas J. Sargent, professor of economics at New York University and the 2011 Nobel Prize in Economics. The title of the paper that he presented was &ldquo;Taxes, Debts, and Redistribution&rdquo;. The second keynote lecture was given by Tobias Adrian, Senior Vice President and Function Head Capital Markets Function at the Federal Reserve Bank of New York. The title of the paper that he presented was &ldquo;Intermediary Leverage Cycles and Financial Stability&rdquo;. The last keynote lecture was given by V&iacute;tor Gaspar, Director of the Fiscal Affairs Department at the International Monetary Fund. The title of the paper that he presented was &ldquo;Fiscal Policy and Macro-Systemic Risks&rdquo;. All keynote lectures have been followed by a very active general discussion.</p>

<p>download pdf file of the conference&nbsp;program <a href="/files/files/MACFINROBODS-conference%20Paris%20-%20final%20program22June2015.pdf">here</a><br />
<br />
